All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Enum Summary 
    Class Description
    Argument
    Represents an argument
    ArgumentMismatchEvent
    An event that is provided by ArgumentMismatchEventListener
    ArgumentMismatchEventListener
    A listener that gets triggered when an argument is not valid
    ArgumentResult
    This class converts a value into the given type with parsing string values and using ArgumentResultConverter
    ArgumentResultConverter
    Converter interface
    BadCategoryEvent
    An event that is provided by BadCategoryEventListener
    BadCategoryEventListener
    A listener that gets triggered when a CategoryLimitable command used in wrong category
    BadChannelEvent
    An event that is provided by BadChannelEventListener
    BadChannelEventListener
    A listener that gets triggered when a ChannelLimitable command used in wrong channel
    CategoryLimitable
    Commands that implements this interface can be limited for categories
    CategoryLimitation
    Represents a specific type of limitation
    ChannelArgument
    An argument that has a regex that only accepts inputs what are channel tags
    ChannelLimitable
    Commands that implements this interface can be limited for channels
    ChannelLimitation
    Represents a specific type of limitation
    ComboArgument
    Represents an argument that has multiple choices, and they are the only valid values for the user to pick The values are key value pairs The key is String and the value can be String or Long
    Command
    A class that represents a command
    CommandActionEvent
    An event that is provided by CommandActionEventListener
    CommandActionEventListener
    A listener that gets triggered when on every usage of a command
    CommandActionListener Deprecated.
    because of the new event system use CommandActionEventListener instead
    CommandBuilder<B extends CommandBuilder<B>>
    Useful class that makes Command creations more comfortable
    CommandBuilder.ConcatenatorBuilder
    A nested class that unifies parameters of Command.addConcatenator(Concatenator, Argument...) for CommandBuilder.concatenators(ConcatenatorBuilder...)
    CommandErrorListener Deprecated.
    because of the new event system use BadCategoryEventListener, BadChannelEventListener and ArgumentMismatchEventListener instead
    CommandErrorType Deprecated.
    see CommandErrorListener for more information
    CommandEvent
    The base class of every event that contains the minimum information that is provided with events
    CommandHandler
    The main class of the API
    CommandResponder
    A class that takes methods out from SlashCommandInteraction that are to respond to a command
    Concatenator
    Concatenates the arguments' result to a type of value that based on the concatenation process The process is implemented by subclasses overriding Concatenator.concatenate(ArgumentResult...) method
    ConstantArgument
    Only accepts inputs that are exactly the same as its name
    GroupArgument
    Represents an argument with SUB_COMMAND_GROUP type that only can contain ConstantArgument This is for grouping SUB_COMMAND options because SUB_COMMANDS cannot be nested
    InputArgument
    Represents argument that can have multiple value depends on the user input and the restrictions of the argument These arguments can be optional
    Limitation<T>
    Represents a command limitation
    MentionArgument
    An argument that has a regex that only accepts inputs what are mention tags
    NumberArgument
    An argument that only accepts number inputs inside long's range
    RoleArgument
    An argument that only accepts role as input and returns a Role
    RoleLimitable
    Commands that implements this interface can be limited for roles
    RoleLimitation
    Represents a specific type of limitation Commands with this limitation do not work in private
    ServerCommand
    A Command that only can be used on servers where the command has been registered.
    Can be limited for users, roles, channels and categories.
    ServerCommandBuilder
    Useful class that makes ServerCommand creations more comfortable
    StringArgument
    An argument that only accepts any string value
    StringConcatenator
    Represents a type of Concatenator that concatenates the arguments' result to a String separated with a delimiter
    SubArgument<T extends Argument>
    Represents a sub argument Classes that extends this class can have arguments
    TypeConcatenator
    Represents a type of Concatenator
    URLArgument
    An argument that only accepts URL inputs
    URLConverter
    Converts to URL from the given value that is expectedly is a valid URL.
    UserLimitable
    Commands that implements this interface can be limited for users
    UserLimitation
    Represents a specific type of limitation Commands with this limitation do not work in private
    ValueArgument
    Represents an argument that accepts a specified type of value
